22/03/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski, the chairman of the ruling Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia, has set up a meeting with leaders of the main parties Tuesday (22 March), aimed at ensuring fair runoff local elections on Sunday. 
The government wants to avoid a repetition of irregularities registered in some municipalities during the first round on 13 March. 
Nikola Gruevski, leader of the main opposition VMRO-DPMNE, is refusing to attend the meeting.
Also Tuesday, a seminar on transborder co-operation in Southeast Europe starts in Skopje. 
The focus is co-ordination among regional police authorities for better border management. 
(Makfax, Macedonian government Web site - 22/03/05; A1 TV - 21/03/05)
